```

The `\tableofcontents` command generates the table of contents based on the sectioning commands (e.g., `\section`, `\subsection`, etc.) in your document. In this example, I've also included some customizations for the section commands using the `titlesec` package. These customizations change the font size and spacing of the sections to make them more visually appealing. However, these customizations are not required to generate the table of contents. Simply including the `\tableofcontents` command at the beginning of your document is enough to generate it automatically.

